abstract: A handful of great titles are leaving the service for U.S. subscribers soon, including a bona fide comedy classic. See them while you can.
snippet: A handful of great titles are leaving the service for U.S. subscribers soon, including a bona fide comedy classic. See them while you can.
lead_paragraph: This month’s selection of titles leaving Netflix in the United States are a typical esoteric assortment of big-budget studio flicks and indie dramas, but the comedies are what really make this one stand out — including an anticapitalist satire and one of the very first stand-up spotlights the service ever funded. Let’s start there. (Dates indicate the final day a title is available):

main: Stream These 8 Movies Before They Leave Netflix in February

abstract: Transcripts released by the House Jan. 6 committee showed nearly two dozen witnesses invoking their right against self-incrimination, underscoring the hurdles to the investigation.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House committee investigating the Jan. 6 attack on the Capitol released a batch of 34 transcripts on Wednesday that showed witnesses repeatedly stymying parts of the panel’s inquiry by invoking their Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination.

abstract: Every so often, a specific boot gets associated with a certain era. Will Blundstone’s Chelsea boots be the defining style of the early 2020s?
snippet: Every so often, a specific boot gets associated with a certain era. Will Blundstone’s Chelsea boots be the defining style of the early 2020s?
lead_paragraph: Perhaps what recently happened to Jenn Stimple, a wardrobe stylist for TV and film, has also happened to you. Ms. Stimple said that after a colleague complimented her shoes — a pair of Chelsea boots from Blundstone — she pointed out that several people on set were wearing the same style. “If you look around, that person has them on, and that person has them on, and that person,” she said she told her colleague.

print_headline: Boots Made for Comfort, and for Coveting

abstract: The decision barring the takeover of a big video game publisher is a major victory for proponents of regulating tech giants, which have faced obstacles in the United States.
snippet: The decision barring the takeover of a big video game publisher is a major victory for proponents of regulating tech giants, which have faced obstacles in the United States.
lead_paragraph: British antitrust regulators dealt a major setback on Wednesday to Microsoft’s plans to acquire the video game giant Activision Blizzard for $69 billion, blocking the proposed deal and handing a notable win to government enforcers around the world who want to rein in Big Tech.

main: U.K. Blocks Microsoft’s $69 Billion Bid for Activision, a Blow for Tech Deals
print_headline: U.K. Blocks Microsoft’s Acquisition of Activision

abstract: A new push by the Kremlin frames the war as a counterterrorism operation and seeks to rally Russians to support the fight, officials and researchers say.
snippet: A new push by the Kremlin frames the war as a counterterrorism operation and seeks to rally Russians to support the fight, officials and researchers say.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Since before the war, Russia has spread disinformation about its need to stamp out Nazism in Ukraine. But in recent days, Moscow’s propaganda has shifted, arguing that it is battling terrorism and falsely accusing Ukraine of planning a dirty bomb attack as part of that narrative.

main: Russia Intensifies Its Propaganda Campaign Against Ukraine
print_headline: Russian Propaganda Frames War as Against Terror

abstract: One lawsuit described a work atmosphere of drinking, drug use and sexual harassment. Another accused the group of failing to pay overtime.
snippet: One lawsuit described a work atmosphere of drinking, drug use and sexual harassment. Another accused the group of failing to pay overtime.
lead_paragraph: Project Veritas, a conservative group known for using covert recordings to embarrass its political opponents, has agreed to settle two federal lawsuits that accused it of underpaying employees and having a “highly sexualized” work atmosphere.

main: Project Veritas Settles Suits That Portrayed It as Mistreating Its Employees
print_headline: Project Veritas Settles 2 Suits  Over Its Treatment of Its Staff

abstract: Tetris exploded in popularity after a race in the 1980s to secure global rights for the Soviet-made video game, a tale retold in a new movie. It is still captivating minds decades later.
snippet: Tetris exploded in popularity after a race in the 1980s to secure global rights for the Soviet-made video game, a tale retold in a new movie. It is still captivating minds decades later.
lead_paragraph: Rotating a colorful shape before slotting it into the perfect position is such a satisfying experience that Tetris has joined chess in the pantheon of universally recognizable games.

abstract: Former President Donald J. Trump’s continuing presence on the political scene has prompted the appointment of a third special counsel.
snippet: Former President Donald J. Trump’s continuing presence on the political scene has prompted the appointment of a third special counsel.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General Merrick B. Garland’s appointment on Friday of Jack Smith, a longtime prosecutor, as a special counsel to oversee two criminal inquiries involving former President Donald J. Trump renewed attention on a position that has played a significant role in politically charged investigations in recent years. Here’s a closer look.

main: What Is a Special Counsel? Here’s What You Need to Know.
